menu "BLE Configuration"

config BLE_DEVICE_NAME
    string "BLE device name (advertised name)"
    default "HatefulBlue"
    help
        The name advertised over BLE and shown in iOS Settings > Bluetooth.
        Maximum 31 characters (BLE advertisement payload limit).

config NIMBLE_LOG_LEVEL
    int "NimBLE runtime log level (0=NONE,1=ERROR,2=WARN,3=INFO,4=DEBUG,5=VERBOSE)"
    default 2
    help
        Select the runtime log level for the NimBLE host. Lower values reduce
        console spam from GATT/ATT operations. The value maps directly to
        esp_log_level_t used by esp_log_level_set().

config DIAG_NOTIFY_INTERVAL_SEC
    int "Diagnostic NOTIFY interval (seconds, 0 = disabled)"
    default 30
    range 0 300
    help
        How often (in seconds) the BLE diagnostic characteristic pushes an
        updated JSON report to subscribed clients via NOTIFY.
        Set to 0 to disable periodic notifications entirely — READ still
        works on demand at any interval.

endmenu

menu "GPS Configuration"

config GPS_DIAG_LOG
    bool "Enable GPS diagnostic logging"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, the GPS task emits a periodic 30-second health summary
        (chars, checksums, satellites, HDOP, fix state, baud) and logs every
        fix-state transition, satellite-count change, and 1 Hz position fix
        to the console via ESP_LOGI.
        Disable to reduce console output in production builds while keeping
        all UART error/warning and watchdog messages intact.

endmenu

menu "Buzzer Configuration"

config BUZZER_ENABLED
    bool "Enable passive buzzer audio alerts"
    default y
    help
        Play a 5-second audio alert on GPIO 45 when a notification or
        incoming call is received.  Uses the LEDC PWM peripheral to drive
        the passive buzzer at the correct frequency — do NOT use with an
        active (self-oscillating) buzzer wired to this pin.
        Disable to silence the buzzer entirely without affecting display
        or BLE behaviour.

endmenu